SIROON MANGURIAN; MEZZO-SOPRANO, CERAMIST 
Siroon Mangurian, 83, a mezzo-soprano who enjoyed a career on Los Angeles 
operatic stages in the 1930s but then began creating ceramic vessels in ethnic 
styles and stylized figures of owls and faceless people which proved popular in 
La Cienega galleries. Miss Mangurian, a native of Armenia, performed with the 
Los Angeles Philharmonic and with the old Los Angeles Grand Opera. In Redondo 
Beach on April 13. 
